main event: Observers watched an unidentified flying object with red and green lights near Corvallis, Oregon in December 1966.
interesting points: The object exhibited various courses and changed in direction and size during observation., The sighting lasted for 3 minutes., The reported object was described as having different appearances, sometimes with lights and other times as a solid object., The Air Force deemed the report insufficient for a definitive conclusion., This incident was part of three sightings within an eight-minute span.
sighted object: unidentified flying object with red and green lights
witness description: Observers included local individuals, one being a school teacher.
